<TITLE> Fire in Mirpur kills 1 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 12 (bdnews24.com) A fire broke out at the Kazi Bari slum at Shah Ali thana in capital's Mirpur early Friday, killing a young man and gutting around 100 shanties. The dead has been identified as Ilin, 35. Fire official Shahana Perveen told bdnews24.com that the fire broke out at around 4 in morning and it about an hour and half to douse the blaze. The fire was apparently caused by a mosquito coil, she said. Shah Ali thana police chief Abdur Rashid said Ilin was a waiter at a local restaurant. His body has been taken by his relatives. bdn
